{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"<xsl:sort>","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/XSLT/Element/sort","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div style=\"background:#f5f5f5; margin: 5px 0;\" id=\"sect1\">\n    <b><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XSLT/Transforming_XML_with_XSLT/The_Netscape_XSLT_XPath_Reference\">XSLT/XPath Reference</a></b>: <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XSLT/Element\">XSLT elements</a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/EXSLT\">EXSLT functions</a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Functions\">XPath functions</a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Axes\">XPath axes</a>\n</div>\n<p>The <code>&lt;xsl:sort&gt;</code> element defines a sort key for nodes selected by <code>&lt;xsl:apply-templates&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;xsl:for-each&gt;</code> and determines the order in which they are processed.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: xml notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token namespace\">xsl:</span>sort</span>\n  <span class=\"token attr-name\">select</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span>EXPRESSION</span>\n  <span class=\"token attr-name\">order</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>ascending<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">|</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">\"descending\"</span>\n  <span class=\"token attr-name\">case-order</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>upper-first<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">|</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">\"lower-first\"</span>\n  <span class=\"token attr-name\">lang</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span>XML:LANG-CODE</span>\n  <span class=\"token attr-name\">data-type</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>text<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">|</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">\"number\"</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">/&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"required_attributes","title":"Required Attributes","isH3":true,"content":"<p>None.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"optional_attributes","title":"Optional Attributes","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"select\"><code>select</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Uses an XPath expression to specify the nodes to be sorted.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"order\"><code>order</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Specifies whether the nodes should be processed in \"<code>ascending</code>\" or \"<code>descending</code>\" order. The default is \"<code>ascending</code>\".</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"case-order\"><code>case-order</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Indicates whether upper- or lowercase letters are to be ordered first. The allowable values are \"<code>upper-first</code>\" and \"<code>lower-first</code>\".</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"lang\"><code>lang</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Specifies which language is to be used by the sort.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"data-type\"><code>data-type</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Defines whether items are to be ordered alphabetically or numerically. The allowable values are \"<code>text</code>\" and \"<code>number</code>\" with \"<code>text</code>\" being the default.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"type","title":"Type","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Subinstruction, always appears as a child of &lt;xsl:for-each&gt;, where it must appear before the template proper or of &lt;xsl:apply-templates&gt;.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"defined","title":"Defined","isH3":true,"content":"<p>XSLT, section10.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"gecko_support","title":"Gecko support","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Supported.</p>"}}],"toc":[],"summary":"The <xsl:sort> element defines a sort key for nodes selected by <xsl:apply-templates> or <xsl:for-each> and determines the order in which they are processed.","popularity":0.0002,"modified":"2022-09-09T05:38:45.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"sort","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"<xsl:sort>","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"sort","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/xslt/element/sort","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/xslt/element/sort/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/f22e42182591e38590c9add80de91a51bce3cde2","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/XSLT","title":"XSLT: Extensible Stylesheet Language Transformations"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/XSLT/Element","title":"XSLT elements reference"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/XSLT/Element/sort","title":"<xsl:sort>"}],"pageTitle":"<xsl:sort> - XSLT: Extensible Stylesheet Language Transformations | MDN","noIndexing":false}}